def_cn: (演出或比赛等的)满座，爆满
def_en: If a play, sports event, or other entertainment is a sell-out, all the tickets for it are sold.

def_cn: (对原则的)背弃;(向敌对势力的)屈服
def_en: If you describe someone's behaviour as a sell-out, you disapprove of the fact that they have done something which used to be against their principles, or given in to an opposing group.
